<h1>CSS Theme System Enhancements - January 2025</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>This document outlines significant improvements made to the Comserv CSS theme system, including the implementation of an interactive CSS editor, enhanced theme management capabilities, and improved CSC admin access controls.</p>

<h2>Major Changes Implemented</h2>

<h3>1. Interactive CSS Theme Editor</h3>

<p><strong>New Feature</strong>: Interactive CSS editing interface with real-time preview capabilities.</p>

<p><strong>Key Components Added</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>/Comserv/root/admin/theme/edit_css_interactive.tt</code> - Main interactive editor template</li>
<li><code>/Comserv/root/static/css/theme-editor.css</code> - Enhanced styling for editor interface</li>
<li><code>/Comserv/root/static/js/theme-editor.js</code> - Interactive JavaScript functionality (924 lines)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Functionality</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Real-time CSS editing with syntax highlighting</li>
<li>Live preview panel showing changes instantly</li>
<li>Theme variable management with visual controls</li>
<li>Background image selection and positioning</li>
<li>Color picker integration</li>
<li>Save/preview workflow with validation</li>
</ul>

<h3>2. Enhanced Theme Management Controller</h3>

<p><strong>File Modified</strong>: <code>/Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Admin/Theme.pm</code></p>

<p><strong>Enhancements Made</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Added <code>edit_css_interactive</code> method for enhanced editor interface</li>
<li>Implemented CSC admin access controls (CSC sees all themes, others see site-specific themes)</li>
<li>Enhanced logging throughout theme operations</li>
<li>Improved error handling with Try::Tiny integration</li>
<li>Added CSS variable extraction and merging utilities</li>
<li>Color analysis utilities for theme optimization</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>CSC Admin Logic</strong>:</p>
<pre>
# CSC gets access to all themes
if ($is_csc) {
    @available_themes = sort keys %$themes;
} else {
    # Non-CSC sites only get their own theme(s) + generic themes
    foreach my $theme_key (keys %$themes) {
        if ($theme_key eq $current_theme || 
            $theme_key eq 'default' || 
            $theme_key =~ /^generic/i ||
            $theme_key eq $site_name) {
            push @available_themes, $theme_key;
        }
    }
}
</pre>

<h3>3. Improved CSS File Structure</h3>

<p><strong>New CSS Files Added</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>/Comserv/root/static/css/themes/component_styles.css</code> - Component-specific styling</li>
<li><code>/Comserv/root/static/css/themes/site_themes.css</code> - Site-specific theme definitions</li>
<li><code>/Comserv/root/static/css/themes/themes.css</code> - Master theme file</li>
<li><code>/Comserv/root/static/css/theme-overrides.css</code> - Theme override capabilities</li>
<li><code>/Comserv/root/static/css/theme-previews.css</code> - Preview-specific styling</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Enhanced Existing Files</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Updated theme-specific CSS files (csc.css, apis.css, usbm.css, etc.)</li>
<li>Improved CSS variable usage throughout theme files</li>
<li>Better organization of theme-related styles</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. Template Toolkit Plugin Integration</h3>

<p><strong>Achievement</strong>: Successfully integrated Template Toolkit 2 plugin with PyCharm IDE.</p>

<p><strong>Configuration Added</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Updated <code>Comserv2.iml</code> with 12+ TTK2 template directories</li>
<li>All <code>/Comserv/root/</code> subdirectories now recognized as template directories</li>
<li>Improved IDE support for .tt file editing and syntax highlighting</li>
</ul>

<h3>5. Theme Configuration Improvements</h3>

<p><strong>Enhanced Features</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Centralized theme definitions in <code>/Comserv/root/static/config/theme_definitions.json</code></li>
<li>Improved theme mapping handling in Git operations</li>
<li>Better error handling and logging for theme operations</li>
<li>Site-specific theme access controls</li>
</ul>

<h2>Technical Improvements</h2>

<h3>1. CSS Variable System</h3>

<p><strong>Implementation</strong>: Enhanced use of CSS custom properties (variables) for dynamic theming.</p>

<p><strong>Example Variables</strong>:</p>
<pre>
--primary-color: #0056b3;
--secondary-color: #f9f9f9;  
--accent-color: #FF9900;
--text-color: #000000;
--background-color: #ffffff;
--nav-bg: #ccffff;
--button-bg: var(--accent-color);
--header-bg: var(--primary-color);
</pre>

<h3>2. Interactive Editor Features</h3>

<ul>
<li><strong>Real-time Preview</strong>: Live preview panel updates as CSS is modified</li>
<li><strong>Visual Property Editing</strong>: Click-to-edit interface for theme properties</li>
<li><strong>Background Management</strong>: Advanced background image and positioning controls</li>
<li><strong>Color Harmony</strong>: Intelligent color selection with contrast analysis</li>
<li><strong>Variable Extraction</strong>: Automatic detection and management of CSS variables</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Access Control Enhancement</h3>

<p><strong>CSC Admin Privileges</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Access to all available themes across all sites</li>
<li>Advanced editing capabilities</li>
<li>Full theme management permissions</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Regular Site Access</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Limited to site-specific themes</li>
<li>Access to default and generic themes</li>
<li>Restricted editing permissions</li>
</ul>

<h2>Files Modified/Added</h2>

<h3>Core Application Files</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Admin/Theme.pm</code> - Enhanced controller functionality</li>
<li><code>Comserv/root/admin/theme/edit_css_interactive.tt</code> - New interactive editor template</li>
</ul>

<h3>CSS and JavaScript Files</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>Comserv/root/static/css/theme-editor.css</code> - Editor-specific styles</li>
<li><code>Comserv/root/static/js/theme-editor.js</code> - Interactive editor functionality (924 lines)</li>
<li><code>Comserv/root/static/css/theme-overrides.css</code> - Override capabilities</li>
<li><code>Comserv/root/static/css/theme-previews.css</code> - Preview styling</li>
<li><code>Comserv/root/static/css/themes/themes.css</code> - Master theme file</li>
<li><code>Comserv/root/static/css/themes/component_styles.css</code> - Component styling</li>
<li><code>Comserv/root/static/css/themes/site_themes.css</code> - Site-specific themes</li>
</ul>

<h3>Configuration Files</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>Comserv2.iml</code> - PyCharm project file with TTK2 plugin configuration</li>
<li>Theme definition files in <code>/Comserv/root/static/config/</code></li>
</ul>

<h2>Usage Instructions</h2>

<h3>1. Accessing the Interactive Editor</h3>

<p><strong>URL</strong>: <code>/admin/theme/edit_css_interactive</code></p>

<p><strong>Requirements</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Admin role required</li>
<li>CSC users see all themes, others see site-specific themes</li>
</ul>

<h3>2. Using the Interactive Editor</h3>

<p><strong>Steps</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Navigate to the theme editor URL</li>
<li>Select theme from dropdown (if available)</li>
<li>Use the CSS editor panel to modify styles</li>
<li>Preview changes in real-time in the preview panel</li>
<li>Click "Save Changes" to persist modifications</li>
<li>Use "Preview" button to test changes before saving</li>
</ol>

<h3>3. Theme Variable Management</h3>

<p><strong>Available Controls</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Color pickers for primary theme colors</li>
<li>Background image selection and positioning</li>
<li>Typography and spacing controls</li>
<li>Border and shadow adjustments</li>
</ul>

